Benefits of a cold plunge:
•Reduces inflammation and swelling
•Relieves sore muscles
•Supports immunity
•Improves mental health

Today felt good! More than good…amazing really. One of the hardest parts of this postpartum journey has been my physical fitness. It has been such a major part of my life but most importantly in my adult life. All women (I assume)  go through an identity crisis postpartum and I was no different. Let’s do a little 16 week postpartum update shall we?

It’s been a journey so far! It’s all been pretty much how I expected it to be. Drastic changes in the beginning after birth and now a slow and steady decline. A few things to note about lifestyle and stats pre and post baby.

Labor Day Stats:
Weight: 208
Body Fat: 26%
Visceral fat (fat around belly/organs): 13

16 weeks PP
Weight: 172.6
Body Fat: 21%
Visceral Fat: 8

I don’t have a goal weight in mind, I never do. But I do know body fat will continue to decrease as time goes on as well as tummy fat. Ideally my BF will be within a range of 16-18 and visceral fat will be 5-6. I currently only go to the gym 2x a week and do daily outdoor walks + daily yoga. Nutrition is clean eats and I took out red meat just until mid March. Eventually I’ll be back to the gym 5 days a week but for now, slow and steady is winning the race!

#postpartumjourney #16weekspostpartum #postpartumhealth #nutritioncoach #fitnesscoach

Stuffed Bell Peppers! Chefs kiss amirite?!

One of my favs because it’s easy and delicious! Recipe below!

Ingredients:
8 bell peppers-cleaned out and rinsed
1 lb ground Turkey (or beef) (I used 99% lean Turkey)
1 packet taco seasoning
Chopped onion 
1 can corn
1 can black beans
Mild cheddar shred cheese
Sour cream
Salsa

Set oven to 350°
Cook peppers for 15-29 minutes upside down 

While peppers cook, brown ground Turkey. Add taco seasoning and onion, simmer. Add in corn and black beans. When done, flip peppers right side up, fill with ground Turkey mix. Sprinkle in shred cheese, bake until cheese bubbles. Too with sour cream and salsa.

I paired with rice and refined beans but feel free to swap out for other sides!

Try these 3 push day exercises! Incorporating CORE in every single exercise is the goal! Controlled movement and bracing your core throughout all of these!

Chest press + leg lifts: press the lower back into the bench, controlled chest press. Breath out as you bring the legs and arms up.

Single arm shoulder press + single leg balance: forces you to SLOW down in order to hold your form. 

Supine triceps extension + alt leg extension: again press that lower back into the bench, elbows high, breathing out with each extension.

Give these a go and let me know what you think! 🤘🏾

Balance! Every. Single. Day.
Why? Yes because I love it but also…
It engages my core and I would rather start working on balance now before I get older. 99% of my older clients want to work on balance to prevent falls. Why wouldn’t you work on it now rather than when it could potentially be a problem? 

I know I’m nowhere near the age to worry about falls but ever since tearing both of my ACL’s, balance and stability have been part of my exercise regime. Even if you don’t consistently go to the gym, balance can be worked on in the comfort of your own home. ☺️

All you need is a pair of dumbbells for this quick full body workout! 
1. Sumo squat + hammer curl + press (toes slightly out, head and chest tall, squeeze glutes at the top)
2. RDL into bent over row (slight bend in the knees, push the hips back, lead with the elbows)
3. Chest fly + pike (push lower back into mat, core tight)
4. Skull crusher + leg extension (elbows stay high, again press lower back into mat)

3-4 rounds, set of 15-20 each exercise. Pick a weight that you can complete all 4 exercises with and don’t drop the dumbbells until each set is over, then take your break! 💪🏾

Comin atcha with a sweaty AMRAP sesh!

Coming up on my year postpartum I have been IN MY FEELS. Not only celebrating a year of life for my daughter but also the STRUGGLE that it has been to feel like me in my own body. Although I feel strong and have made progress, I am human and still get in my head about where I thought I would be in a years time. 

The human body is amazing and especially a woman’s body. Movement is my way to thank my body for all that it has been through! With all that rambling….try out this AMRAP! Set the clock for 30 minutes and get through as many rounds as possible. Take breaks as you need but push yourself! It was a doozy! 🫠🫠 I should have recorded before the circuit 😅 Also, I definitely went too heavy for the weight but once I started I wasn’t about to decrease 🤦🏽‍♀️

DB thrusters-15 
DB chest press + leg lift-15
Box jumps-15
DB skull crushers + leg lifts-15
MB slams-10

POV as a first time mama!

I thought I knew love….until I became a mother. Wow…literally a love like no other! 🥺 
Labor…my oh my…hardest thing I’ve even had to do…worse than both ACL surgeries but if I had to do either again, hands down would choose labor 😳
Speaking of labor…have a birth plan but be flexible if needed!
The emotions….the just keep flowing. 😂
Everything my child does is cute…I don’t care what it is! 🙃
Each stage is my favorite, literally can’t decide! 🥰
Breastfeeding is a journey in itself. Thankful to have made it a year nourishing my baby. 🙏🏽
Everyone has an opinion/advice…even if ya don’t ask for it. 😆
I’ll never hold or cuddle my baby “too much”. 😌
I could watch her sleep for hours. 🥹
Mama is my favorite title! 🥲

Thank you KayLynn Mac Warren for the best year of my life!
